value: Breeds in northern Asia south of the Arctic Circle from the upper Yenesei to Kamchatka, south to northern Mongoha(?), the Amur and Ussuriland. Winters in Japan, Korea, eastern and southern China to upper Burma.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Primarily in fresh-water on and around ponds, small lakes and quiet rivers; forages and winters also in rice fields.
